note: Ogbah has struggled this season and is in line to see a sharp reduction in snaps with Bradley Chubb now in town. He may have deep league bye week filler appeal for Week 9, but fantasy managers will want to make other plans where feasible.

Pitre continues to impress, most recently racking up five solos, one assist, and two tackles for loss against the Tennessee Titans. He has been an elite DB2 option this season but can be trusted as a DB1 option during this heavy bye week. He may not have another DB1 overall level game in store, but he is an elite option for Week 9 thanks to a plus matchup against a Philadelphia Eagles team allowing the most fantasy points per game to the position. Roster and start Pitre in all competitive leagues.

Holland exploded with 10 solos, two assists, and one pass defended in Week 8 and is back to being a DB1 option now that he is playing a box-heavy role. Holland is a must-start as long as he remains in this fantasy-friendly role.

CJGJ went nuts in Week 8, tallying seven solos, one assist, one sack, one tackle for loss, one interception, and one pass defended. Big play C.J. has been on fire over the last three weeks and is a must-start while he is this hot. His transition back to safety has been seamless, and one has to wonder just how good the Saints' defenses in years past could have been, had they played him at his real position. Treat him as a DB1 option until he cools down, especially this week against David Mills and a Houston Texans offense surrendering the 23rd most fantasy points to the safety position.

Owens appeared to have been benched in favor of Eric Murray last week, but head coach Lovie Smith said that he remains the starter. However, Lovie likened Murray to a relief pitcher, suggesting that this may become a trend. The snap uncertainty and benching drop Owens from DB1 consideration to DB3 land.

Amani Hooker is dealing with a shoulder injury and may miss more games for the Titans, putting Adams right back in the mix as a DB3 with DB2 upside for a plus Week 9 matchup against the Kansas City Chiefs.

Forrest should see his snaps increase with Cole Holcomb set to be sidelined for Week 9. Jamin Davis should see more snaps than usual, but Forrest will also see an uptick in box snaps against the Minnesota Vikings, making him a sneaky DB3 option for those in a bye week pinch.
